               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Libānos “Vita of Libānos” (fols. 1ra-44vb)&#xD; II) Taʾammǝra
                     Libānos “Miracles of Libānos”: 11 miracles (fols. 45ra-54ra)&#xD; III) Mälkǝʾa
                     Libānos “Image of Libānos”: 28 strophes (fols. 55ra-58ra).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For the Gadla Libānos, Taʾammǝra Libānos and Malkǝʾa Libānos compare: A.
                        BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003 (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe
                        105, 106]).</note>
                     <note>- Text I.</note>
                     <note>Of this text, there are three different recensions (cp. Bausi 2003,
                        XIII-XX):</note>
                     <note>1) GETATCHEW HAILE, “The Homily of Abba Elǝyas, Bishop of Aksum, on
                        Mäṭṭa”, ABoll 108, 1990, 29-47.</note>
                     <note>2) ALESSANDRO BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003a
                        (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]), 1-72 [text] and 1-45 [tr.].</note>
                     <note>3)CARLO CONTI ROSSINI, “Il Gadla Libânos”, in: Ricordi di un soggiorno in
                        Eritrea. Fascicolo Primo, Asmara 1903, 25-34.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The text in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm012">MGM-012</ref>seems more
                        closed to the text as in the so called second recension, but with some more
                        passages in the initial part.</note>
                     <note>Certainly, it is needed a further and accurate investigation.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The text is attributed to ʾElyas, the Bishop of Aksum (mention on <locus target="#17ra">17ra</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The text contains, on <locus target="#1ra">1ra-</locus>vb, a rhymed
                        prologue:</note>
                     <note>በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፨ በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡ ዘአምቅድመ፡ ዓለም፡ ህላዌሁ፨
                        ወእስከ፡ ለዓለም፡ ዘኢየሐልቅ፡ ምስፍናሁ። ልዑል፡ በልዕልናሁ፨ ስብሕ፡ በስብሐቲሁ፨ ...</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>- Text II.</note>
                     <note>The miracles are 11; with the exception of the miracle 1, all the others
                        are wrongly numbered.</note>
                     <note>All the miracles are also contained in Bausi 2003 (s. above); here we
                        give the correspondence as follows [on the left, the miracles in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm012">MGM-012</ref>, with the indication of the
                        folios containing them; on the right, the miracles in Bausi’s edition, with
                        the specific number and the equivalent number of the verse (§) given in the
                        edition]:</note>
                     <note>Miracle 1 (<locus from="46ra" to="46va">46ra-46va</locus>) = Bausi,
                        Miracle 2, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES203204">203-204</ref>,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES206207">206-207</ref>(without the additional
                        passages found in Mss. AD = § 205)</note>
                     <note>Miracle 2 [numbered as 3] (<locus from="46va" to="47va">46va-47va</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 3, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES208211">208-211</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 3 [numbered as 4] (<locus from="47va" to="48rb">47va-48rb</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 4, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES212214">212-214</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 4 [numbered as 5] (<locus from="48rb" to="48va">48rb-48va</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 5, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES215216">215-216</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 5 [numbered as 6] (<locus from="48va" to="49va">48va-49va</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 6, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES217221">217-221</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 6 [numbered as 7] (<locus from="49va" to="50rb">49va-50rb</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 7, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES222225">222-225</ref>(without the additional passages found in Mss. AD = §
                        226)</note>
                     <note>Miracle 7 [numbered as 8] (<locus from="50rb" to="50va">50rb-50va</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 8, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES227228">227-228</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 8 [numbered as 9] (<locus from="50va" to="51rb">50va-51rb</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 10, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES251255">251-255</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 9 [numbered as 10] (<locus from="51rb" to="52ra">51rb-52ra</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 32 (<ref type="mss" corresp="ES372374">372-374</ref>; in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm012">MGM-012</ref>, after § 374 only few lines are added)</note>
                     <note>Miracle 10 [numbered as 11] (<locus from="52rb" to="52vb">52rb-52vb</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 33, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES376378">376-378</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>Miracle 11 [numbered as 12] (<locus from="52vb" to="54ra">52vb-54ra</locus>) = Bausi, Miracle 11, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES256261">256-261</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>On <locus from="45ra" to="46ra">45ra-46ra</locus>, the miracles are
                        preceded by a praise in honour of the Saint (= Bausi, “Preambolo”, §§<ref type="mss" corresp="ES182186">182-186</ref>).</note>
                  </msItem>
